procedures.name: Venipuncture
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), and clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation).

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour collection for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and clinically significant findings.

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Medical History Review
procedures.label: Medical History
procedures.description: Collection of participant medical history, demographics, Wilson disease history, and prior treatment history.

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurements
procedures.label: Height, Weight, BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Infectious Disease Screening
procedures.label: HIV, Hepatitis B and C screen
procedures.description: Blood test to screen for Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV), Hepatitis B, and Hepatitis C.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Urine/Serum Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine or serum test to detect pregnancy in females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: Cannula Placement
procedures.description: Placement of a cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Collection and follow-up of adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Bowel and Urine Monitoring
procedures.label: Bowel/Urine Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring of urination and bowel movements, including menstruation checks for women.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Device
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Catheter
medicalDevices.label: Catheter
medicalDevices.description: A catheter may be used for venous access but not left in place for longer than 72 hours.
